        "solutionCode": "num1 = int(input())\nnum2 = int(input())\nresult = num1 > num2\n\n# Read two numbers and an operator from input\nnum1 = int(input())\nnum2 = int(input())\noperator = input().strip()\n\n# Perform the operation\nif operator == '+':\n    result = num1 + num2\nelif operator == '-':\n    result = num1 - num2\nelif operator == '*':\n    result = num1 * num2\nelif operator == '/':\n    result = num1 / num2\nelse:\n    result = 'Invalid operator'\n\n# Print the result\nprint(result)"
